-- HSBC Bank Sells A$4.25 Million of 3.5% Uridashi Notes
-- B y   H a r u m i   I c h i k u r a
-- 2012-01-24T15:42:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-24/hsbc-bank-sells-a-4-25-million-of-3-5-uridashi-notes.html
The following uridashi bond went
on sale. Uridashi bonds are debt issued in the euromarket
and sold mainly to Japanese individual investors.  Issuer:              HSBC Bank plc
Amount:              A$4.25 million
Coupon:              3.5 percent
Duration:            Five years
Sales period:        Jan. 23 - Feb. 21
Settlement date:     Feb. 23, 2012
Maturity:            Feb. 23, 2017
Uridashi Manager:    Jyoko Shoken  Hirota Securities  To contact the reporter on this story:
Harumi Ichikura in London at   hichikura@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
